See the "sudoers" man page (or online at https://www.sudo.ws/man/1.8.19/sudoers.man.html) for full details of the format of these files.

Simple example, permitting the jenkins user to run "/usr/bin/something arg1 arg2 ...argN" as root without a password:

jenkins ALL= (root) NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/something arg1 arg2 ...argN
